{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} – a deer. Current form is highly abstracted – legs have transformed to {{zh-l|*比}} – note grouping of front and rear legs, which are bent – head has transformed to middle component (similar to {{zh-l|*凸}}/{{zh-l|*曲}}), while antlers on top and extended lip/mouth on left transformed into {{zh-l|*广}}. This transformation occurred during seal characters.

Contrast the very different development of {{zh-l|*馬|horse}}, and the transformation in {{zh-l|*𢊁}} (as in {{zh-l|*薦}}), which has the head of {{lang|zh|鹿}} but the legs of {{lang|zh|馬}} ({{zh-l|*灬}}).
